#jaishankar #mygov 

Co-presented to you by ‚Å†@MyGovIndia

In this exceptional episode of The Ranveer Show Podcast, we are pleased to welcome one of the most prestigious personalities of the Government of India, Dr. Subrahmanyam Jaishankar. He is an Indian diplomat and politician, serving as the Minister of External Affairs of the Government of India.

In this informative episode, Dr. Subrahmanyam Jaishankar talked about topics that are closely related to Geopolitics. He shares his experience of working with Prime Minister Narendra Modi and what are the challenges he has to face as the Minister of External Affairs. He further discusses the Role of Artificial Intelligence and Quantum Computing in the field of Geopolitics and put light on the situation of Brain Drain in the Country. 

This is one of the most special episodes that I‚Äôve been a part of considering my interest in Geopolitics and India‚Äôs bright future. Being in conversation with Dr. Subrahmanyam Jaishankar was an overwhelming yet fantastic experience. 

I hope you enjoy this episode. Feel free to comment down any thoughts you have about the whole conversation.

snippet.title: Tiku Weds Sheru - Official Trailer | Nawazuddin Siddiqui, Avneet Kaur | Prime Video India
snippet.description:
Prime Video Presents
Tiku Weds Sheru Official Trailer
Directed by Sai Kabir
Starring Nawazuddin Siddiqui and Avneet Kaur
Produced by Kangana Ranaut

Official Release Date June 23, 2023 on Prime Video 

About:
Sheru and Tiku are marginalized souls from the underprivileged strata of society. They are ambitious for a better life but, life has different plans for them. Shiraz, popularly known as Sheru, hails from Bhopal, a small-town in India. Sheru comes to Mumbai in search of a better life. Being semi-literate, he works as a pimp for a local don, Shahid Bhai, and also as a junior artist as a decoy job, where he finds girls for his pimping business. Episode 3798: Yellow Shagun Ceremony

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Meerab is an ambitious and beautiful young girl who wants to pursue higher studies. Her entire world revolves around her parents and she believes in them the most. Her strong and confident personality makes her stand against social injustices around her.

On the contrary, Murtasim hails from a powerful and influential family. He respects and values the morals and traditions of his family and refuses to let the family down.

Meerab‚Äôs life takes an unexpected turn when she finds out about her family‚Äôs decision regarding her and Murtasim‚Äôs life. Meerab‚Äôs hatred towards Murtasim continues to grow as a family secret from the past resurfaces. Coming from different backgrounds and mindsets, Murtasim begins to realize Meerab‚Äôs arrogant behaviour towards him and begins to consider her a challenge for himself. On the other hand, Meerab who is used to living her life on her own terms refuses to accept Murtasim‚Äôs family traditions and unnecessary social barriers.

Soon their lives go through a series of emotional sufferings and misunderstandings where it becomes difficult for them to coexist. Despite their hatred towards each other, will Meerab and Murtasim accept their true feelings or will the dynamics of ego and self-respect force them to stay apart?

snippet.title: Barsaat Aa Gayi (Video) Javed-Mohsin| Shreya Ghoshal,Stebin Ben | Hina Khan, Shaheer Sheikh|Kunaal V
snippet.description:
VYRL Originals is now ready to unveil their new single to welcome the rains in 2023. After the massive triple successes of Baarish (2020) Baarish Ban Jaana (2021) and Baarish Aayi Hai in 2022, we now give you "Barsaat Aa Gayi". 

Composed by the talented composer duo Javed Mohsin, written by wordsmith Kunal Vermaa and sung in the stunning voices of Shreya Ghoshal and Stebin Ben . Barsaat Aa Gayi also reunites the superhit on-screen pair of Hina Khan and Shaheer Sheikh, from their previous successful collaboration of Baarish Ban Jaana. 

Get ready for the monsoon song of 2023 - Barsaat Aa Gayi

snippet.description:
Enjoy the video of our new punjabi song " Blackia " by Geeta Zailda, Gurlej Akhtar in which music is given by Jassi X & the Lyrics of this latest punjabi song are penned by Kabal Saroopwali

Make sure to give us a Thumbs Up if you Like the Song..... Enjoy & Stay Connected with us :) 

#punjabisong #newpunjabisongs #latestpunjabisongs 

‚ô™Song : Blackia
‚ô™Singer : Geeta Zaildar                                                                                                                                               
‚ô™Co - Singer : Gurlej Akhtar
‚ô™Music : Jassi X
‚ô™Lyrics : Kabal Saroopwali
‚ô™Female Lead : Harleen Utradhi
‚ô™Film by : Harry Singh, Preet Singh
‚ô™Music Label : T-Series

Lyrics :

Je main gaddi lai li khnde paisa kithon aayea
Je shaunk poore khnde maal ae bakayea
Gurlej ..jehde jattan aiven Tere ser charde
Geeta zaildar...

Malla thalle goddeyan de dharange jrur
Gurlej...ohh pind wale khnde aa black krda
Geeta zaildar ...aaje ta ni kiti par krange jrur
Geeta zaildar..ohh boli la ke chakki aa breed saltan di

Lalli shalli krlu ki rees jatt saan di
Hik utte dhar k ni note jane maddiyan nu
Mehfil di golak bhari ni aapan bhaan d
Gurlej...jina dian hikkan utte tu lad da

Geeta zaildar.. aaje ta ni lade par ldange jrur
Gurlej..ohh pind wale khnde aa black krda
Geeta zaildar.. aaje ta ni kiti par krange jrur ...
Geeta zaildar..ohh hauli hauli hall jatta sare ajmanvage borderon leavnge te borderon tapamge..

Khulli turi phiru chandi dian dabbian ch .
Mathi mathi belliyan di kharsh hattanvge ..
Gurlej..jatta tu ta bhare aa truck nottan de..
Geeta zaildar... aaje ta ni bhare par bharange jrur

Gurlej.. pind wale khnde aa black krda..
Geeta zaildar.. aaje ta ni kiti par krange jrur ..
Geeta zaildar.. mehnata da poora paisa kothi utte laggea ..
Appan kise saale de ni batuye cho kaddea..

Sade kehda daade ni c tauti kiti lokkan di ..
Hera feri karke ni sada mudd bhjea
Gurlej... chona vich khado kabal saroopwali da
Geeta zaildar.. aaje ta ni irada par khddange jrur ..

Gurlej.. pind wale khnde aa black krda
Geeta zaildar.. aaje ta ni kiti par krange jrur.....!

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Episode 3799: Sapna Ki Love Story
--------------------------------------------------------
Everyone has arrived together to perform the shagun ritual of Pyaarelal and Sapna, but Pyaarelal seems to be missing. Someone said that he had visited the nearby temple before the ritual. Pyaarelal returns shortly, but he is accompanied by another young man named Swapnil. Sapna gets flabbergasted when she sees this new fellow. Pyaarelal talks about how he met Swapnil. Swapnil turns out to be Sapna's ex-boyfriend, who left her for a lucrative job offer in Canada. Swapnil's job didn't work out, and now he has returned, but Sapna has moved on. According to Pyaarelal, Swapnil and Sapna still have feelings for each other, so he decides to unite them. Will Pyaarelal sacrifice for Sapna's love story this time?

Episode 3800: Tapu Sena Ki Outstation Trip
--------------------------------------------------------
Pyaarelal reunites Sapna and Swapnil while continuing to be single. In an effort to cheer him up, Tapu Sena visits their favorite Pyaarelal uncle. Pyaarelal makes the decision to stop using his new name and resumes using his old one, Popatlal. Jetha does the Surya Namaskar to begin his day, but Tapu surprises him. Jetha declines Tapu's request to accompany him on an adventure when he tells him he wants to do so with Tapu Sena. Tapu informs Jetha that this trip is not enjoyable; rather, it is an environmentally responsible one. Where trees have been cut down, Tapu Sena has made the decision to plant saplings in their place. Will Tapu be able to take this trip with Jetha's approval?
